                    <death when="0376" syriaca-computed-start="0376-01-01" source="#bib1099-2">376</death>
                    <state type="martyr" source="#bib1099-2">
                        <p>Martyr</p>
                    </state>
                    <note xml:lang="en" type="abstract" xml:id="abstract-en-1099">ʿAbdā Alaha, priest, was tortured
            with <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1100">ʿAbdishōʿ</persName> by Ardashir,
          brother of Sapor; ʿAbdā was arrested with seven friends and seven virgins. Barḥaḏbshabā
          and Samuel also were executed. Then ʿAbdishōʿ and ʿAbdā Alaha were executed. They were
          buried by Byzantine slaves in a neighboring village. He was martyred with 38
          companions.</note>
                    <event type="veneration" source="#bib1099-2">
                        <desc>The saint is venerated on 16 May in East Syrian church.</desc>
                    </event>
                    <event type="attestation" xml:id="attestation1099-1" source="#bib1099-2">
